abstract.p:
Integrability of a linearly damped two-coupled non-linear oscillators equation 
					\begin{align*}
					\ddot{x} &= -d\dot{x} -\alpha x -\delta_{1}(x^{2}+y^{2})-2\delta_{2}xy,\\
					\ddot{y} &= -d\dot{y}-\beta y - \delta_{2}(x^{2}+y^{2})-2\delta_{1}xy
					\end{align*}
					is investigated by employing the Painlevé analysis. The following two integrable cases are identified: (i) $d=0$, $\alpha=\beta$, $\delta_{1}$ and $\delta_{2}$ are arbitrary. (ii) $d^{2}=25\alpha/6$, $\alpha=\beta$, $\delta_{1}$ and $\delta_{2}$ are arbitrary. Exact analytical solution is constructed for the integrable choices.

