There are currently two hints for new physics involving CP violation in $b ightarrow s$ transitions: $\Delta S \equiv S_{f} - S_{J/\phi K} 
eq 0$, and difference in direct CP asymmetry $\Delta A_{K\pi} \equiv A_{K^{+} \pi^{0}} - A_{K^{+} \pi^{-}} 
eq 0$. We explore the two scenarious with a large and unique new CP phase in $b \leftrightarrow s$ tansitions. Motivated by $\Delta S 
eq 0$, we update on the right-handed strange-beauty squark $	ilde{sb}_{1R}$ at TeV scale. Motivated by $\Delta A_{K\pi} 
eq 0$, we explore sequential fourth generation $t'$ and $b'$ quarks. Both scenarious can survive constraints such as SM level $b ightarrow s\gamma, s\ell\ell$ and $B_{s}$ mixing, and predict sizable CP violation in $B_{s}$ mixing. The fourth generation picture predicts sizable $K_{L} igtharrow \pi^{0} 
u
u$. Direct search for $	ilde{sb}_{R}$, $b'$ and $t'$ at hadronic colliders, such as Tevatron Run II and LHC, can complement further CP violation studies at these machines, as well as at the future Super $B$ factory.

The surface water waves in a water tunnel can be described by systems of the form [Bona and Chen, \textit{Physica} D116, 191 (1998)] 
					\begin{equation*}
					\begin{cases}
					 v_t + u_x + (uv)_x + au_{x x x} − bv_{x x t} = 0,\\
					 u_t + v_x + u u_x + cv_{x x x} − d u_{x x t} = 0,
					\end{cases} \tag{1}
					\end{equation*} where $a$, $b$, $c$ and d are real constants. In general, the exact travelling wave solutions will be helpful in the theoretical and numerical study of the nonlinear evolution systems. In this paper, we obtain exact travelling wave solutions of system (1) using the modiﬁed tanh–coth function method with computerized symbolic computation.
